Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with channel estimation and tracking, which are important topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of a multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) system, which is a key technology in wireless networking. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper focuses on the performance of high-speed mobile communications, which is a subfield of communication and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper presents an equivalent channel model and system model, which are related to systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses spatial multiplexing, which is a technique used in multimedia communication systems.
